----------------------------------------------------------------------
README
----------------------------------------------------------------------


step-by-step tutorial:

1. create mesh:

   - run cubit GUI:
     > claro
     
     then run meshing script: 
     claro -> Menu "Tools" -> "Play Journal File" ... and select file 
                                          "2lay_mesh_boundary_fig8.py"
    
     this creates all the mesh files in directory MESH/
     

2. decompose mesh files:

    - copy to directory OUTPUT_FILES/ in decompose_mesh_SCOTCH directory 
    
    - specify number of partitions (nparts, equals number of CPUs to run simulation with)
      in file "constants_decompose_mesh_SCOTCH.h" 
      
    - run decomposer in directory decompose_mesh_SCOTCH/:
      > ./compile_all.csh
      > ./a.out 
            
    - copy mesh partitions "proc0000***_Database" to directory "LOCAL_PATH"  
      specified in "Par_file"     


3. generate databases:

    - compile generate_databases:    
      > make xgenerate_databases
     
    - submit job script:
      > qsub go_generate_database_pbs.sesame.bash
      
4. run simulation:

    - compile specfem3D:
      > make xspecfem3D
      
    - submit job script:
      > qsub go_solver_pbs.sesame.bash


      